article.headline: Lander scores 22 as Western Kentucky beats Campbellsville 101-77
article.description: — Khristian Lander's 22 points helped Western Kentucky defeat Campbellsville 101-77 on Wednesday night.
article.linkText: Lander scores 22 as Western Kentucky beats Campbellsville 101-77
article.story: BOWLING GREEN -- — Khristian Lander's 22 points helped Western Kentucky defeat Campbellsville 101-77 on Wednesday night. Lander added five rebounds for the Hilltoppers (5-3). Brandon Newman scored 15 points while going 5 of 10 from the floor, including 3 for 6 from 3-point range, and 2 for 3 from the line, and added seven rebounds. Tyrone Marshall had 15 points and shot 5 for 8, including 3 for 4 from beyond the arc. The Tigers were led in scoring by Cobe Penny, who finished with 21 points. Jace Wallace added 19 points, seven rebounds and six assists for Campbellsville. In addition, Tyrelle Hunt had 14 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
